11/10/2002
TIRANA, Albania -- The opposition confirmed on Thursday (10 October) its readiness to co-operate with the ruling Socialist Party in institutional reforms. Prime Minister Fatos Nano, who leads the Socialist Party, met with Democratic Party chairman Sali Berisha. President Alfred Moisiu also attended, and according to a statement issued by his office, both party leaders confirmed their determination to lead Albania towards Euro-Atlantic integration and maintain political dialogue to that end. As for planned constitutional amendments affecting election laws, both Nano and Berisha said they would seek solutions appropriate to all political parties. (ATA - 10/10/02)
